The trial for Russell Henderson, accused in the beating death of Matthew Shepard, was postponed to April 6 due to a scheduling conflict.
Henderson and Aaron McKinney face murder charges and the death penalty if convicted.
The case has sparked discussions on hate crimes and bias legislation.
Jury selection began amidst a backdrop of national attention and pressure.
Henderson's defense claims he was a mere witness, not a participant in the brutal attack.
The trial's significance extends beyond the courtroom, highlighting the need for societal change and justice for victims of hate crimes.
